			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">What would i change here to make it so that the sentry gun only fires on who fires upon me. If i walk near somone and they don't attack me it doesn't attack him</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Store a CBaseEntity in your Player CBasePlayer called LastEnemy, and in TakeDamage in Player.cpp get the pevAttacker and check if the Player thats being attacked is you. Get the CBaseEntity of the pevAttacker andstore it as the lastenemy. Then override the sentry guns enemy by setting its Enemy to LastEnemy.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">ALso i need help with where to place the UTIL functions at the very start ( first 2 paragraphs) and where to add the CbaseEntity part for the sentry in player.h . I'm still learning so please bear with me </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
UTIL functions go in the util.cpp and write their prototypes in util.h
<br />

<br />
CBaseEntity *m_Sentry goes in CBasePlayer in player.h (I did say "You will also need to add a "CBaseEntity *m_Sentry" in Player.h in CBasePlayer, and set it to NULL when you spawn" :p)</span><span class=sign><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://rcbot.bots-united.com" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">RCBot</span></a> | <a href="http://forums.bots-united.com" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Bots United</span></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span>
